{
  "stem": "1550.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "For the rest of the period, as far as I know, it was never allowed-- it was never permitted for women to stay overnight in the men's camp.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, what happened [LAUGHS] once was we had a radio in the camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the radio was tuned into the BBC from London.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, of course, since the language in the camp was mostly German, we were only allowed to-- to-- to listen to the German language broadcasts of the BBC London. 'Here, East London,' [SINGING] bah, bah, bah, bah bah bah.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was every day.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a news bulletin at 8 o'clock, and at 10 o'clock, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so we had-- there were loud speakers at certain parts in the camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But there was one central radio room where there was the radio.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was also a gramophone where we had some records, where we could play some records for entertainment.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there was at one time, a ship was sunk by a U-boat in the Indian Ocean.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was a rumor amongst the native population that we have a radio transmitter in the camp and we had been in touch with enemy U-boats.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And because we are German speaking-- these people didn't know about Jews and stuff-- we are German agents, you know, who are in touch with the Germans, and we have a radio in the camp.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, of course, we had only a receiver, not the transmitter, you understand?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So-- so-- but the British had to do something about this rumor.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So what they did-- they-- there was-- there were never any roll reports, because you couldn't escape there anyway, right?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Even if you were-- even if you went over the wall and into the-- to outside, you can't escape from that island.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
